      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is absolutely true that the immediate threat of business closures represents a tangible and permanent economic harm to workers and local communities. Focusing solely on abstract future environmental benefits ignores the immediate, verifiable suffering of those currently employed. A balanced view acknowledges that while environmental goals are important, the government must also ensure that regulatory burdens do not disproportionately crush the very small businesses that form the backbone of a local economy. Therefore, the certainty of job loss must be weighed as a major, immediate policy failure if not mitigated.",
